Defendant Jordan Devon Roby in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Student Intern Daniel Murphy under the supervision of Zach Wittchow for Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 8 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 3 days credit CONCURRENT to any other sentence/count with Good Time.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 3 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 3 days credit CONCURRENT to any other sentence/count with Good Time.


Court STAYED the sentence in Counts 1 & 2 and placed the defendant on 18 MONTHS probation.  Court allows for dosage probation.

  Conditions of Probation:
- 4 months and 2 weeks condition time with Huber &  Day Reporting Center. Court stayed commencement until 04/08/2016 by 5pm.
- AODA assessment and cooperate with any programs deemed necessary by the probation department.
- Absolute/maintain sobriety, no alcohol, no drugs.
- No possession/consumption/selling/distribution of illegal drugs/alcohol.
- Random urine screens.
- Obtain/maintain fulltime employment/education/vocation.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- Follow all rules of supervision and follow through with any other treatment deemed necessary by the department.

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
All court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA); 
All applicable fees of supervision.
-  Cash bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.

Defendant Jordan Devon Roby in court with attorney Richard Jeffrey Carpenter.  Katherine Seelow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for final pre-trial, however parties would like to proceed with a plea hearing instead.  Jury trial date of 3/14/16 is vacated.
AS TO ALL COUNTS:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

Case is adjourned for sentencing in Branch 22.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for March 28, 2016 at 08:30 am.
